1
00:00:02,086 --> 00:00:05,133
<i>(birds chirping)</i>

2
00:00:05,193 --> 00:00:09,586
Oh, good morning little friends,
your singing is oh so pretty.

3
00:00:10,246 --> 00:00:12,326
Yes, it is a very
beautiful day today,

4
00:00:12,653 --> 00:00:14,826
certainly something
worth singing about.

5
00:00:15,353 --> 00:00:19,293
♪ There's music in the treetops
and there's music in the vale. ♪

6
00:00:19,626 --> 00:00:23,460
<i>♪ and all around me</i>
<i>music fills the sky ♪</i>

7
00:00:23,966 --> 00:00:25,866
<i>♪ There's music by the river </i>

8
00:00:26,006 --> 00:00:28,060
<i>♪ and there's music</i>
<i>in the grass ♪</i>

9
00:00:28,193 --> 00:00:32,393
<i>♪ And the music makes your</i>
<i>heart soar in reply ♪</i>

10
00:00:32,826 --> 00:00:35,273
<i>♪ Aahhhh! </i>

11
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:36,366
(growl)

12
00:00:36,387 --> 00:00:41,068
<i>♪ Aaaaahhh! </i>

13
00:00:41,475 --> 00:00:43,526
<i>♪ Ah ha ha! Ah ha ha! </i>

14
00:00:43,596 --> 00:00:45,734
<i>♪ Aaaaah! </i>

15
00:00:45,811 --> 00:00:50,640
<i>♪ Ah ha ha! Ah ha ha! </i>

16
00:00:50,675 --> 00:00:53,865
<i>♪ (ends on a sweet high</i>
<i>note) ♪</i>

17
00:00:54,579 --> 00:00:57,283
<i>(cheers)</i>

18
00:00:57,353 --> 00:01:00,800
Oh, thank you so much.
You're too kind.

19
00:01:01,635 --> 00:01:03,116
<i>Pinkie Pie: WOW!</i>

20
00:01:06,387 --> 00:01:11,088
Oh. You um, you didn't
hear me, um ...

21
00:01:11,571 --> 00:01:13,673
Singing in the most
beautiful voice ever?

22
00:01:13,862 --> 00:01:15,456
Uh, yeah we did!

23
00:01:17,481 --> 00:01:18,608
<i>(whimper)</i>

24
00:01:25,834 --> 00:01:30,830
Subtitles by YayPonies
http://yayponies.eu
HoH version

25
00:01:59,651 --> 00:02:03,593
Wow! I've never heard you
sing a solo like that before.

26
00:02:04,051 --> 00:02:06,396
It was like a little
slice of heaven.

27
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:08,633
With ice cream on top!

28
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:12,912
Fluttershy, I cannot believe
your spectacular voice

29
00:02:12,947 --> 00:02:15,228
isn't part of the
Pony Tones Quartet!

30
00:02:15,782 --> 00:02:17,622
Um...well...I...

31
00:02:17,676 --> 00:02:19,408
Especially since you're
having us perform

32
00:02:19,433 --> 00:02:22,019
for your Ponyville Pet Center
Fundraiser tomorrow night!

33
00:02:22,803 --> 00:02:24,934
Well, you see, I...

34
00:02:25,014 --> 00:02:27,219
This simply must be rectified!

35
00:02:27,430 --> 00:02:29,824
You must share that
stunning voice at the event.

36
00:02:29,913 --> 00:02:31,936
Yeah! It will be so amazing!

37
00:02:32,153 --> 00:02:34,793
You'd be there on stage,
basking in the hooflights,

38
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:38,076
the center of attention,
a shining star...

39
00:02:38,220 --> 00:02:40,979
<i>With everypony staring</i>
<i>at you, judging you,</i>

40
00:02:41,024 --> 00:02:43,529
jealously noting how they
could be WAY better than you.

41
00:02:43,539 --> 00:02:45,632
Why wasn't it them?
Why wasn't it them?

42
00:02:45,737 --> 00:02:48,035
<i>And then, when you choke,</i>
<i>they'll turn on you</i>

43
00:02:48,044 --> 00:02:49,660
becoming a seething angry mob

44
00:02:49,830 --> 00:02:51,388
and you'll be horribly
humiliated,

45
00:02:51,644 --> 00:02:54,582
never able to show your
face in Ponyville again!

46
00:02:54,729 --> 00:02:58,393
Pinkie Pie! Don't
be ridiculous!

47
00:02:59,337 --> 00:03:00,700
But I'm so good at it!

48
00:03:01,792 --> 00:03:02,844
Come, Fluttershy.

49
00:03:02,988 --> 00:03:06,025
You will join the group making
the Pony Tones Quartet

50
00:03:06,313 --> 00:03:08,112
the Pony Tones Quintet!

51
00:03:08,662 --> 00:03:09,360
No!

52
00:03:09,971 --> 00:03:11,024
Pardon me?

53
00:03:11,523 --> 00:03:13,174
I love the Pony Tones.

54
00:03:13,414 --> 00:03:14,934
I'm one of their biggest fans.

55
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:17,424
But I do not want to
perform with them.

56
00:03:17,907 --> 00:03:19,286
Why not, Fluttershy?

57
00:03:19,635 --> 00:03:26,729
Well you see, I...I
have...um...I-I have...

58
00:03:26,918 --> 00:03:27,644
Spit it out!

59
00:03:28,588 --> 00:03:31,126
I have...stage fright!

60
00:03:31,657 --> 00:03:32,579
<i>(gasp)</i>

61
00:03:32,598 --> 00:03:33,692
Is it contagious?

62
00:03:34,099 --> 00:03:36,297
Stage fright isn't
a disease, Pinkie.

63
00:03:36,646 --> 00:03:38,806
It just means that Fluttershy
is scared to perform

64
00:03:38,819 --> 00:03:39,884
in front of everypony.

65
00:03:40,288 --> 00:03:42,016
I'm very thankful
the Pony Tones

66
00:03:42,028 --> 00:03:43,961
are singing at the Pet
Center Fundraiser.

67
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:46,646
<i>And I'm really looking</i>
<i>forward to the performance.</i>

68
00:03:47,004 --> 00:03:49,564
But I'll be watching
safely from the audience.

69
00:03:50,336 --> 00:03:54,288
Well, I think it's a terrible
waste of an exquisite talent,

70
00:03:54,752 --> 00:03:56,563
but I understand that
you're not comfortable.

71
00:03:57,312 --> 00:03:57,993
Thank you.

72
00:03:58,675 --> 00:03:59,881
Ooh! Angel's right!

73
00:04:00,048 --> 00:04:00,995
We better get going!

74
00:04:01,232 --> 00:04:03,817
There's a lot of work to
do before tomorrow's event!

75
00:04:06,563 --> 00:04:16,384
♪

76
00:04:16,499 --> 00:04:17,318
Ahem!

77
00:04:17,392 --> 00:04:20,713
All right, Pony Tones, let's
run through that again!

78
00:04:21,625 --> 00:04:22,326
<i>(pitch pipe tone)</i>

79
00:04:22,393 --> 00:04:26,857
<i>♪ (doo wop bass notes) </i>

80
00:04:26,931 --> 00:04:31,353
<i>♪ (vocalizing in harmony) </i>

81
00:04:31,366 --> 00:04:35,228
♪ Everypony's saying you should
<i>learn to express your voice. ♪</i>

82
00:04:35,235 --> 00:04:38,336
<i>♪ But if talk doesn't seem</i>
<i>like it's the answer ♪</i>

83
00:04:38,441 --> 00:04:40,099
<i>♪ luckily you have a choice. </i>

84
00:04:40,204 --> 00:04:45,344
<i>♪ When you find you've got the</i>
<i>music, got the music in you. ♪</i>

85
00:04:45,395 --> 00:04:49,808
<i>♪ Find you've got the music</i>
<i>got the music in you. ♪</i>

86
00:04:50,595 --> 00:04:51,651
<i>(sigh)</i>

87
00:04:53,020 --> 00:04:54,451
Whoo hoo! Yeah!

88
00:04:54,678 --> 00:04:56,265
Rarity, you were awesome!

89
00:04:57,148 --> 00:05:00,230
Thank you, Spike, but
this is an ensemble.

90
00:05:02,118 --> 00:05:04,249
Enh, the rest of you
were pretty good, too.

91
00:05:04,950 --> 00:05:08,240
Oh, I thought you were all
amazing, Pony Tones.

92
00:05:08,633 --> 00:05:09,804
Thanks, Fluttershy!

93
00:05:10,281 --> 00:05:12,800
Now, Pony Tones, I want you
all to rest your voices

94
00:05:12,828 --> 00:05:13,843
for the remainder of the day.

95
00:05:14,041 --> 00:05:16,326
We'll do a final run-through
tomorrow before the big event.

96
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:17,075
All right?

97
00:05:17,344 --> 00:05:17,897
Eeyup.

98
00:05:18,265 --> 00:05:19,180
Sounds great!

99
00:05:19,846 --> 00:05:22,793
Oh, Rarity, the Pony Tones
are really going to make

100
00:05:22,803 --> 00:05:25,747
the Ponyville Pet Center
Fundraiser so special!

101
00:05:26,054 --> 00:05:29,472
Thank you so much for
helping me help the animals!

102
00:05:29,513 --> 00:05:32,665
Oh yes. It is wonderful
when a plan comes together

103
00:05:32,678 --> 00:05:34,822
without any sort of
drama, isn't it?

104
00:05:35,264 --> 00:05:36,316
<i>(giggle)</i>

105
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:39,071
<i>(owl hoots)</i>

106
00:05:39,657 --> 00:05:41,948
<i>(rooster crows)</i>

107
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:55,897
♪

108
00:05:55,910 --> 00:05:57,100
Morning, Fluttershy.

109
00:05:57,472 --> 00:05:59,331
Good morning,
Pony Tones!

110
00:05:59,574 --> 00:06:02,819
Actually, we're the Pony
Tones minus one tone.

111
00:06:03,056 --> 00:06:05,392
Big Mac is
inconveniently late.

112
00:06:06,464 --> 00:06:11,801
<i>(panting)</i>

113
00:06:11,923 --> 00:06:12,985
Well, there you are!

114
00:06:13,228 --> 00:06:15,062
Have I not told you
about punctuality?

115
00:06:15,513 --> 00:06:17,456
Ah! I don't want
to hear it!

116
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:20,873
<i>♪ (pitch pipe tone) </i>

117
00:06:21,448 --> 00:06:25,484
<i>♪ (no doo wop introduction) </i>

118
00:06:25,756 --> 00:06:26,496
(gulp)

119
00:06:29,904 --> 00:06:32,422
Big Mac! Can you please
start the song?

120
00:06:34,179 --> 00:06:35,292
Nnope.

121
00:06:35,577 --> 00:06:36,214
Big Mac!

122
00:06:36,576 --> 00:06:37,664
Did you lose your voice?

123
00:06:37,763 --> 00:06:38,307
<i>(gulp)</i>

124
00:06:38,496 --> 00:06:39,536
Eeyup.

125
00:06:39,894 --> 00:06:42,083
<i>(gasps)</i>

126
00:06:43,936 --> 00:06:45,971
♪

127
00:06:45,987 --> 00:06:48,380
Whatever did you
do to cause this?

128
00:06:48,709 --> 00:06:50,041
Well...

129
00:06:51,977 --> 00:06:53,161
Howdy, everypony!

130
00:06:53,299 --> 00:06:56,521
And welcome to the 12th Annual
Ponyville Turkey Call!

131
00:06:56,550 --> 00:06:58,563
<i>(cheering)</i>

132
00:06:58,582 --> 00:06:59,878
<i>(gobble)</i>

133
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:01,708
Who will take the
title this year?

134
00:07:02,009 --> 00:07:03,251
Will it be somepony new?

135
00:07:03,475 --> 00:07:06,710
Or will the Turkey Call
champion of six years

136
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:10,672
<i>defend his title to make</i>
<i>it lucky number seven?</i>

137
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:13,715
We'll find out if
ya stop yer gabbin'

138
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:16,034
and git on with
the gobblin'!

139
00:07:16,172 --> 00:07:17,507
All right, everypony!

140
00:07:17,852 --> 00:07:19,203
Let's talk turkey!

141
00:07:19,654 --> 00:07:21,459
Big Mac, yer up!

142
00:07:22,368 --> 00:07:23,440
<i>(takes a deep breath)</i>

143
00:07:25,211 --> 00:07:27,979
A Turkey Call?

144
00:07:28,124 --> 00:07:31,577
You lost your voice
doing a...Turkey Call?

145
00:07:31,942 --> 00:07:33,952
Lost his voice and the title!

146
00:07:34,044 --> 00:07:35,158
<i>(Pinkie gobble)</i>

147
00:07:36,689 --> 00:07:38,690
Now we can't
perform tonight.

148
00:07:38,755 --> 00:07:40,729
Wait! What? No!

149
00:07:42,288 --> 00:07:43,372
You have to perform!

150
00:07:43,587 --> 00:07:46,006
Otherwise the fundraiser
will be a disaster.

151
00:07:46,432 --> 00:07:48,848
Well, we cannot perform
tonight with only three voices.

152
00:07:49,171 --> 00:07:50,089
Why not?

153
00:07:50,387 --> 00:07:52,486
It would take rearranging
all the music

154
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:53,673
and we just don't have time.

155
00:07:53,945 --> 00:07:56,073
<i>I'm sorry, Fluttershy,</i>
<i>but I have no remedy</i>

156
00:07:56,083 --> 00:07:57,094
<i>for this situation.</i>

157
00:07:57,510 --> 00:07:58,320
<i>(gasp)</i>

158
00:07:58,937 --> 00:07:59,977
Of course!

159
00:08:00,195 --> 00:08:01,001
A remedy!

160
00:08:01,289 --> 00:08:02,060
Follow me!

161
00:08:08,438 --> 00:08:11,244
<i>(hoarse) Ahhhh!</i>

162
00:08:11,292 --> 00:08:12,192
Hmmm.

163
00:08:12,451 --> 00:08:14,336
Aaahh.

164
00:08:16,358 --> 00:08:18,835
I can cure this
pony that is hoarse,

165
00:08:18,999 --> 00:08:21,700
but it will take
a longer course.

166
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:22,979
Come again?

167
00:08:23,260 --> 00:08:23,846
Hmmm.

168
00:08:24,201 --> 00:08:26,672
I can mix a brew that
will work just right,

169
00:08:27,274 --> 00:08:29,841
but it cannot heal
him by tonight.

170
00:08:29,948 --> 00:08:30,896
Oh no!

171
00:08:31,961 --> 00:08:33,734
Where are we ever going
to find a deep voice

172
00:08:33,744 --> 00:08:35,308
to replace Big Mac's?

173
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,587
<i>(chuckle)</i>

174
00:08:37,684 --> 00:08:40,852
Pardon me, Zecora,
but this is no laughing matter.

175
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:43,088
We need a bass voice for
the harmonies to work!

176
00:08:43,158 --> 00:08:45,290
Without it, the
performance will be ruined!

177
00:08:45,424 --> 00:08:47,827
Please forgive my
strange elation,

178
00:08:47,928 --> 00:08:51,129
but I was not laughing
at your situation.

179
00:08:51,264 --> 00:08:52,038
Then what?

180
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:55,686
Remember when you pony folk
stumbled into Poison Joke?

181
00:08:56,198 --> 00:08:59,180
<i>Miss Fluttershy had</i>
<i>an unusual change,</i>

182
00:08:59,315 --> 00:09:01,216
<i>deepening her vocal range.</i>

183
00:09:01,683 --> 00:09:03,545
(very low voice) I don't
want to talk about it.

184
00:09:05,401 --> 00:09:06,390
Yes, yes!

185
00:09:06,982 --> 00:09:09,510
Your voice became really
low, making it sound like...

186
00:09:10,406 --> 00:09:11,427
Flutterguy!

187
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:14,112
With these leaves,
I can mix a brew

188
00:09:14,128 --> 00:09:16,665
creating the same
effect on you.

189
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:18,990
Zecora, that's fantastic!

190
00:09:19,110 --> 00:09:20,713
Yes! I'll do it!

191
00:09:20,894 --> 00:09:23,328
I'd do anything for the animals!

192
00:09:23,497 --> 00:09:26,086
Why, you'd even
appear on stage!

193
00:09:26,553 --> 00:09:27,888
Oh, except that.

194
00:09:29,763 --> 00:09:31,961
I just can't bring
myself to sing on stage

195
00:09:31,974 --> 00:09:33,324
in front of everypony.

196
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:38,358
What if you sang NOT
in front of everypony?

197
00:09:38,822 --> 00:09:39,350
Huh?

198
00:09:39,612 --> 00:09:42,752
What if Big Mac was on
stage moving his lips

199
00:09:42,816 --> 00:09:46,151
while you're behind the
curtain singing his part?

200
00:09:46,246 --> 00:09:48,051
It would be just like
singing in your house.

201
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,817
<i>Nopony would know it was you.</i>

202
00:09:50,377 --> 00:09:53,449
Even still. I just don't think
I could sing in front of--

203
00:09:53,459 --> 00:09:55,689
You must! For the animals!

204
00:09:55,971 --> 00:09:58,300
<i>(squeaks)</i>

205
00:09:58,857 --> 00:10:03,798
Oh, OK, then...mix it up.

206
00:10:05,078 --> 00:10:11,555
♪

207
00:10:11,564 --> 00:10:13,782
Now do it just
like we practiced.

208
00:10:15,011 --> 00:10:15,772
<i>(gasp)</i>

209
00:10:16,984 --> 00:10:25,657
<i>(crowd</i>
<i>chatters)</i>

210
00:10:25,664 --> 00:10:28,192
Good evening,
citizens of Ponyville!

211
00:10:28,614 --> 00:10:30,608
I want to thank you all
for coming out tonight

212
00:10:30,656 --> 00:10:33,494
and generously supporting
the Ponyville Pet Center!

213
00:10:34,089 --> 00:10:37,289
<i>Thanks to your kindness, pets</i>
<i>are finding loving homes</i>

214
00:10:37,324 --> 00:10:39,964
<i>and we are sure to meet</i>
<i>our fundraising goal!</i>

215
00:10:40,528 --> 00:10:41,520
Where's Fluttershy?

216
00:10:42,028 --> 00:10:42,924
Prob'ly hidin'.

217
00:10:43,289 --> 00:10:45,494
You know how much that
pony hates the spotlight.

218
00:10:45,964 --> 00:10:52,131
So, with no further ado, please
welcome...The Pony Tones!

219
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:57,734
<i>(cheers)</i>

220
00:10:57,814 --> 00:10:58,678
<i>♪ (pitch pipe tone) </i>

221
00:10:58,688 --> 00:10:59,641
<i>(big inhale)</i>

222
00:10:59,769 --> 00:11:01,372
<i>(hoarse inhale)</i>

223
00:11:01,939 --> 00:11:06,368
<i>♪ (bass doo wop intro) </i>

224
00:11:06,502 --> 00:11:15,708
<i>♪ (harmony vocalizations) </i>

225
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:18,016
<i>♪ Hot outside can</i>
<i>you see the sunshine. ♪</i>

226
00:11:18,038 --> 00:11:20,336
<i>♪ Something's in the</i>
<i>air today. ♪</i>

227
00:11:20,348 --> 00:11:22,646
<i>♪ Sky is clear and</i>
<i>you're feeling so fine. ♪</i>

228
00:11:22,659 --> 00:11:24,953
<i>♪ Everything's going</i>
<i>to be a-ok. ♪</i>

229
00:11:24,995 --> 00:11:26,012
<i>♪ You listen carefully </i>

230
00:11:26,419 --> 00:11:29,612
<i>♪ on every corner there's</i>
<i>a rhythm playing. ♪</i>

231
00:11:29,690 --> 00:11:33,925
<i>♪ Then it happens suddenly</i>
<i>the music takes you over ♪</i>

232
00:11:33,939 --> 00:11:36,409
<i>♪ and you find you</i>
<i>got the music. ♪</i>

233
00:11:36,608 --> 00:11:38,720
<i>♪ Got the music in you. </i>

234
00:11:38,838 --> 00:11:43,411
<i>♪ Find you've got the music</i>
<i>got the music in you. ♪</i>

235
00:11:43,452 --> 00:11:45,712
<i>♪ Ohh! </i>

236
00:11:45,770 --> 00:11:49,456
♪ Everypony says that you should
<i>learn to express your voice ♪</i>

237
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:52,604
<i>♪ But if talk doesn't</i>
<i>seem like it's the answer ♪</i>

238
00:11:52,659 --> 00:11:54,339
<i>♪ luckily you have a choice. </i>

239
00:11:54,406 --> 00:11:59,545
<i>♪ When you find you've got the</i>
<i>music, got the music in you. ♪</i>

240
00:11:59,616 --> 00:12:01,833
<i>♪ Find you've got</i>
<i>the music ♪</i>

